06/08/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Macedonian President Branko Crvenkovski and Prime Minister Hari Kostov will pay an informal visit to Belgrade on Friday (6 August). Together with Serbian President Boris Tadic and Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica, they will attend the basketball match between Serbia-Montenegro and the United States at the recently opened Belgrade Arena. The trip was planned during last week's meeting between Crvenkovski and Kostunica at the Prohor Pcinski monastery, on the occasion of Macedonia's national holiday. (Tanjug, Makfax - 05/08/04)
